Alcoholic recidivist drivers should install the 'alcolock'
Interior wants the driver with three administrative penalties for alcoholemia, to have to install in his vehicle a system that prevents the drunk vehicle from starting, or if it does not blow.
The initiative was announced last June and is now included in the annual report of the Attorney General's Office, according to which it is a pilot project that will last one year.
Its purpose is the reinsertion of the driver, so the driver will also receive a course of road re-education.
In the experience, in addition to the Attorney General of Segurida Vial, will participate the General Directorate of Traffic (DGT) and the Foundation Instituto Tecnológico para la Seguridad del Automobil (FITSA).
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists reported more than once for driving drunk again take the car.
The alcoholic would avoid it because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in breathed air and prevents starting the car if the driver does not blow abs; or when a concentration of alcohol is detected it is higher than allowed.
Its cost is more than 1,000 euros and would run on behalf of the sanctioned.
In this sense, a study carried out in the US in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with these devices reduce infringements by up to 65% during the first year of implementation.
And in Spain, it is estimated that it could save 115 people every year.
The measure is subject to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to address such behaviour before it results in criminal offences.
And to facilitate its implementation, since legal reform can be done on an ordinary basis, and yet the necessary reform through criminal means requires reform in an organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial mode, although it has already been piloted in some industrial and public service vehicles.
Precisely tomorrow, the Congress of Deputies will vote tomorrow on an initiative of the PSOE in which it intends to install on the school buses this system, just as it has been carried out in France.
