According to East Coast schedule during the new consultations that lasted until after midnight on Saturday, the leaders of the Congress reached an agreement around the financial rescue package of $700 billion in total, after several days of discussion - reported the Reuters.
We have made significant progress - said Nancy Pelosi, Democratic President of the American Congress, stating that the agreement is only to be formalized in a document.
The commitment made on the package was supported by both presidential candidates, Barack Obama and John McCain.
Henry Paulson, the Minister of Finance, speaking about the outcome of the compromise stated: this program will work and will be efficient but more measures are needed. According to Pelosi, it is not about saving Wall Street, but about turning the economy car around.
The written version of the package was published before the opening of the Asian markets, i.e. Sunday before 8 p.m., according to Washington time (i.e. before 2 p.m. on Monday, according to Central European time), without causing a spectacular jump in the bags.
On the bill called the emergency law for economic stabilization in 2008, the first Monday will vote for the American Congress and then the Senate.
President George W. Bush on Saturday night consulted Pelosi and then the White House also welcomed the news on the deal.
We are pleased with the progress made during the night and we highly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy - said Tony Fratto, the spokesman for the White House.
The program is different from the Bush administration's original proposal to spend all $700 billion to buy bad quality credit fund securities.
Now only half of the $700 billion can be spent, using 250 billion immediately after Congress votes, probably on Monday, of this sum the Ministry of Finance will buy securities of credit fund, bad rating and the destination of another $100 billion depends on the decision of the president.
This programme will be monitored by a special body, in which the President of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The other half of the $700 billion can be spent after a new Congressional decision.
According to the law, the Ministry of Finance can apply a combined tactic: it can simultaneously buy bad loans, mortgages and securities credit fund securities, as well as other "poisonous" credits as well.
The purchase can be made by auctions or directly - the competent persons of the ministry have informed.
The law allows the companies concerned to participate in an insurance program where the financial portfolio guarantees the worrying elements, for which the companies will pay the amount corresponding to the foreseeable damages.
Henry Paulson stated: The law thus secures the necessary financial means, which can even reach $700 billion to meet the urgent needs of the US financial system, be concerned with the purchase of bad financial means, their insurance or the prevention of risks that could lead to the collapse of some large financial institutions.
We do everything necessary to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it - he added.
On the other hand, the heads of the banks that are in trouble and waiting for the help of the State will be able to count on the official limitation of their compensation, which the American slang simply calls gold parachutes.
Only in certain specific cases will payments be limited, and limitations depend on the form of assistance provided by the Ministry of Finance.
The limitation means that if the ministry buys in the framework of an auction, an extra tax will be imposed on the gold parachutes, unless the failed boss of the bank retires.
By directly buying bad credits, the government will aggressively intervene to ensure that bosses' compensations are not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations relate only to new contracts to stimulate participation in the programme as well.
This is the first case in American history that will be in force a legal limitation on the income of directors-general - said the Democrat Barney Frank, president of the congressional commission, responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares from the banks participating in the programme, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, as they will ultimately be able to make profits with the transaction as soon as the economy is recovered and with it the bank.
According to the bill in the next five years the president will have to submit to Congress a proposal on how to return the losses of the financial sector to taxpayers.
Of course on both sides there were those who expressed reservations about the project.
This is not what the American citizens entrusted us, that is, the taxpayers' dollars are not being protected - said the Republican Congressman of California, Darrell Issa.
